ZH: 这个顽固不化的老人总是拒绝接受现代科技。
EN: This stubborn old man always refuses to accept modern technology.

ZH: 她的态度如此顽固不化，根本没有办法改变她的决定。
EN: Her attitude is so stubborn that there is no way to change her decision.

ZH: 他们的意见非常顽固不化，无论怎样劝说也没有用。
EN: Their opinions are so stubborn that no matter how much persuasion is done, it is useless.

ZH: 孩子们非常顽固不化地坚持自己的观点。
EN: The children stubbornly insist on their own views.

ZH: 这只顽固不化的猫从不肯接近陌生人。
EN: This stubborn cat never approaches strangers.

ZH: 他是一个顽固不化的保守主义者，对新观念毫不接受。
EN: He is a stubborn conservative who refuses to accept new ideas.

ZH: 尽管多次失败，他依然顽固不化地坚持自己的计划。
EN: Despite multiple failures, he stubbornly sticks to his plan.

ZH: 这个国家的政府顽固不化地拒绝与其他国家合作。
EN: The government of this country stubbornly refuses to cooperate with other nations.

ZH: 他的顽固不化使得合作变得相当困难。
EN: His stubbornness makes cooperation quite difficult.

ZH: 这种顽固不化的态度不利于解决问题。
EN: This stubborn attitude is not conducive to problem-solving.

ZH: 老板总是顽固不化地坚持自己的决定。
EN: The boss always stubbornly sticks to his decisions.

ZH: 他的思维方式非常顽固不化，不愿意接受其他观点。
EN: His way of thinking is extremely stubborn, unwilling to accept other perspectives.

ZH: 这个人无论别人如何努力，他都是顽固不化的。
EN: No matter how hard others try, this person remains stubborn.

ZH: 这位顽固不化的病人拒绝接受治疗。
EN: This stubborn patient refuses to undergo treatment.

ZH: 面对困难，他很容易变得顽固不化。
EN: In the face of difficulties, he easily becomes stubborn.

ZH: 这个小孩非常顽固不化，不听任何人的劝告。
EN: This child is very stubborn and does not listen to anyone's advice.

ZH: 我的爷爷是个顽固不化的时代保守主义者。
EN: My grandpa is a stubborn traditionalist.

ZH: 她的顽固不化使得我们无法与她沟通。
EN: Her stubbornness makes it impossible for us to communicate with her.

ZH: 他是个顽固不化的人，很难与他达成共识。
EN: He is a stubborn person, it is difficult to reach a consensus with him.

ZH: 这些争论已经持续了很久，他们双方都顽固不化。
EN: These arguments have been going on for a long time, both sides remain stubborn.
